segments.text: 12, 1980, and Tommy Suarez of 5010 Oak Shadows is here, and he's listening to everything that has been said.
Have you in any way been coerced into saying anything, or you're saying this completely on your own?
It's my own free will and it's my firm belief and has been since the day of the assassination in 1963.
Okay.
You were telling me yesterday that
And I can't remember, because when I went back to the house, I wrote some notes down, but I couldn't remember all.
There was something that you had said that had been deleted from the Warren Commission and all the other investigations.
The bulk of that investigation has been sealed.
And I believe the period of time was set at 80 years before they would be opened and displayed to the public.
And if you can believe what you see on television and read in the news and hear on radio, certain individuals who believe there was more than one
gunmen involved and who have played back recorded portions of the incident, some of which were supposed to have been recorded at Dallas Police Headquarters.
And their dispatching mechanism put on tape

Because of the mobile unit's microphone on the motorcycle, one of the Dallas police officers who was riding escort, that there was over shots fired and had been stipulated in the various reports and that some witnesses have claimed that there was a
visual evidence to them of additional gunfire from a knoll long near the book storage building.
I believe this knoll would have been a little bit southwest of the southwest corner of the building and would have
been northwest of the path of the automobile the President and the Vice President were riding in.
I was watching this motorcade proceed through Dallas on television, live, at the time the assassination occurred.
But through that media,
I was not able to hear anything that I could distinguish as sound gunfire.
However, in the transfer from the Dallas Police Station to the Dallas County Jail, which was attempted on Sunday morning,

Once again, I was watching that live on television and I did hear the report of firearms or a reasonable facsimile thereof at the incident that Jack Ruby surged towards Lee Harvey Oswald and Oswald folded over and grasped his midriff
and then reportedly died, practically in the arms of a police captain.
And I did distinctly hear that police captain say, Jack, you son of a bitch, to Jack Rutherford.
Is it common procedure for when they're escorting somebody for a policeman not to be in front of the person that they're escorting out?
Proper procedure for a police officer or anybody else to escort a prisoner is the party that has control of the prisoner walks behind the prisoner.
But in this kind of situation that's transpired there, there was numerous peace officers of all categories there, all around Lee Harvey Osmond.
And had it not been for the familiar sight of Jack Ruby around the Dallas police station over the period of
a couple of free months prior to this occurrence, Ruby would never have been able to even gotten on the grounds.
I see, I see that.
And my question is, do you consider it to have been a proper procedure the way that they were escorting him out?
Nothing wrong with the procedure that they were using to escort him.
Their belief was that everybody had been okay to be there and screamed and were not any threat to the life of the prisoner at all.
He was being properly escorted by the captain of the police on one side of him and some other police official on the other side, a commissioned peace officer.
and they each had a hold of an arm.

That captain had a hold of Oswald's right arm and some other individual had his left arm, and they were walking the captain just barely to his right rear, almost the rest of him and the other officer in a similar position on the left side.
So it wasn't a matter of not having sufficient numbers of security.
and operating in the firm belief that they had screened everybody and that there was nobody that would be any threat to the prisoner present.
And I can't fault the Dallas Police Department on this thing at all, but insofar as they're
they were using to transport it, that I would be somewhat tempted to criticize news media because in the book that the chief police at that time in Dallas wrote and said
which can unseat just about any individual from any public office that they decide to, including any president of the United States.
With such action, if he didn't have this thing in the daytime where the majority of people would be able to watch it going on on television, live, as a burst of
between 2 and 4 o'clock a.m. when practically everybody had been in bed asleep.
I know everybody must be watching it live on television.
Matter of fact, at that time, the local television stations here didn't even operate at that time of the morning.
They shut down.
Some of them don't now.
I wouldn't leave the air until 1 o'clock, 1.30.
And I don't think any of them stay all night.
Still have a shut-out period of some time.
Can you give me any information on this General Walker, who you spoke of earlier?
He was, after he had retired, he had come...
He retired from where?
From the military army.
He was retired, I believe, a major general.
And was very active in the field of politics in the Democrat Party.
And I don't even recall what his first name or initials was.
Okay.

But I refused to concede the idea that B. Harvey Oswald was a spy for the Soviet Union, because a spy for the Soviet Union would not make a point to go and marry a Russian woman and bring her to live in Dallas, Texas.
He tried to be a spy, give me a complete flop, because she didn't have his cover blowed before he ever started.
I mean, you know, when somebody's coming from Russia, they are going to, you know, it's going to bring attention at least to watch him and see what is going on.
Yeah.
I understand that.
By what I understand, that's what you're saying.
He was supposed to have been under some kind of surveillance, but certainly wasn't under that close surveillance at that time.
I mean, he was in Dallas somewhere.
You could undoubtedly find him.
Big problem seemed like to find his wife and family and all that after this thing happened.
They didn't?
They did.
Not only found them, but also found that he was the breadwinner for a place to live for he and his wife in Dallas.
They had been living in Fort Worth, his mother in Dallas, and vice versa.
He was keeping up both homes.
and what he'd like to know is around Mexico City and back, he wasn't supposed to even have a job, period.
No way in the time that anybody knew that at all.
He was financing it.
He was living some kind of way.
And, of course, they claimed they checked this all out and that he had sufficient funds coming in from some source.
I never even know where to have done this all.
And it has never been...
clear in my mind what mode of transportation he used to get to Mexico City, but nobody ever mentioned that.
He drove down there, walked, hitchhiked.
How'd he got there?
On a bus?
He didn't go on a train, because he went across the river end at Roma, if he had.
There wasn't anything for a train to go to Roma about.
Nothing there.
that we needed to transport in that train.
It didn't produce anything.
It was just a rocky area around our little village there on the river.
Okay.
An old city on the opposite side in Mexico used to be in the town or anything like that then.
The nearest place after you got over there was San Pedro, and it was at that time about the same size as Humber was.
Yeah, 1963.
I know it's a pretty good side of the town now, but it sure wouldn't be 1963.
You said that you served in the service from the years of... Could you repeat that again?
When I was in the military?
Right.
From August the 7th, 1940 to July 28th, 1945.
And what was your rank in the military?
highest rank in health and I was sergeant.
I did attend officer candidate school and resigned out of it the day before I was to be commissioned as a personal healer.
You said that you, you say that you know that, I don't know, that relations or something like that in Starr County.
Did you know somebody who lived in Starr County or?
While I was stationed there, the only somebody that I ever knew there, at that time, the city marshal there, a fellow by the name of Sanchez, 1940, 1941, I was real well acquainted with him.
I knew him, I've talked to him a few times, that's all.
I know a lot of people there.
I know that the information has been that the great influx of recent years, the great influx of drugs of various kinds, marijuana, hashish, heroin, a whole bag of tricks.
It was coming through there, and some people built some awful pretty homes, at least that's what they showed to be on the television out on the place that didn't produce anything.
They'd find homes out there anyway, before they'd get no money from the oil there.
Great shakes for grazing cattle.
Probably that area right along there where those homes were.
50 acres might support a county.
Maybe.
And, of course, we never had any hard winter that would support them any time, support them year-round, but it takes so many acres to do it, and I doubt anybody had that many in that area.
There's a lot of very fine homes built all along that road between them for several miles, right out to the edge of Star County.
towards the mission to the east of Riverview City.
Showed these pictures and highway numbers and all this stuff right there.
Along the north of the road were the, what they called them, Skeet Specials.
Railroad tracks ran south of the highway.
These houses seemed to be all, practically all of them on the north side of the road.
Wasn't much of anything.
And certainly nothing but brush and that kind of stuff from there back to the banks of the River Grand.
Army post there, Fort Ringgold, sat right on the bank of the River Grand.
Can you tell me from the time that you started into your police career as to where you have been?

you have worked for for what police for what police agencies you have worked for what police stations or since you have retired since you got out of the military have you always been to the police force right and can you can you tell me i was discharged on a friday
July the 28th, 1945, and Monday morning I went down and answered to an ad in the local paper and applied for a job at the Houston Police Department.
And on the 13th day of August, I was called to the station and sworn in as a police officer and given an assignment to work the VJ day for a...
So the police agency that you have always worked with has been HPD.
Have you ever seen any confidential material that has dealt with any Kennedy-related material?
I don't know.
Without divulging any... Any...

uh written material or anything pertaining to this assassination that is not that's not public we had nothing in our files i had access to any files we had no we had nothing to investigate to make it a file yeah
As far as I know, other than the possibility that he may have passed through some time, we ought to leave him with honors.
If he was ever in Houston, I don't remember that.
John Kennedy was here during that same period.
He was here when they were campaigning for the presidency and all, and then he was here
During that time, when Johnson was here, after he was president, I went out to Hobby Air Force, and was part of the police security out there.
He and Lady Bird came down, and Hubert Humphrey and his wife came with them.
You have told me that LBJ was not in the same car with Kennedy or Conley, and that was perfect.
Kennedy and Conley was in the same car, but as the motorcades went by on television, there was a car they were in, and then you see the president lurch back like this in the seat.
And it seemed like John Conley lurched over this way at the same time, kind of down.
And Jackie Kennedy crawled over the back seat and back on the trunk of the open-top car and seemed to be trying to
do something for the president and the Secret Service.
We ended up running along behind at least one of them climbed up on the trunk of the car and somebody gave some kind of signal and took off and they took off.
And there was the space between that car and the one that Johnson and Layward was in was
Do you, is it your assumption that Conley, do you think that Conley and Kennedy were riding together because
Conley had more prestige than Johnson and that it would be more of a good of an appearance for them to be riding together?
No, I think it was strictly a matter of protocol.
The chief executive of the nation visiting was a guest chief executive of the state.
The same token that the lieutenant governor would have been placed in a different car if the two of them had gone to Washington to see the president.
That's something they rolled around.
The governor and his wife was in the car with the president and his wife to the vice president.
Okay.
While in the military, did you receive any kind of commemoration in the military?
Like what?
Just anything.
Have you ever been given special recommendations?
Not particularly just theater and combat.
the Corps and I did receive a certificate of appreciation from half-age Arnold and then a general of the United States Air Force.
Okay and while you had been on the Houston police force have you ever received any accommodation while you were on there?
Did you receive any kind of accommodations from the Houston Police Department for apartment?
Nothing more than letters of accommodation, a bunch of them, two or one and a half.
Yesterday you said you had some...
some kind of a whole wall full of...
There they are.
Okay.
I want to interrupt.
I'm going to interrupt this for one moment.
Let me say this before we shut this off.
What I have stated here is my opinion and is a result of my own...

investigation as best as i could go through with in this case but it appears to me that i have established a motive for each of the individuals i have named as probable conspirators in this incident the motive of uh of uh lemon baines johnson being
wanting to be President of the United States.
George Parr trying to repay Johnson for procuring presidential pardons for some 20 years of his life.
Lee Harvey Oswald, an opportunity of revenge against John Connolly and Jack Ruby, a strictly religious thing, motivated him.
Okay.
Everything that you have said right now, we discussed yesterday, and I asked your permission if you would be recorded.
And nothing that we have said, nothing that has been said today has been pre-planned out to say.
And you told me this yesterday that this has been your opinion, and I've come up to you to no motive asking...

with no knowledge of mine and I'm just trying to find out I just want to learn your opinion is that correct right and I have expressed this same opinion for the same reasons lots of people over you fully expect to express it
Okay.
Tommy Suarez, this is Tommy Suarez, and he's been sitting here through the entire interview on both sides of the tapes, and he's listened to both sides of the tapes.
And have we stopped?
Have we stopped or have we edited anything in any way?
No.
No, I'm saying, have we stopped or have we edited anything?
No.
Okay, okay.
And right now, I'm going to cut this off because I want to go see what he was telling me about, about what you have on your wall.
And we'll resume the cinema.
You're lying, I'm sorry.
Everything that you said today, we've not deleted anything out of this tape and
I've taken pictures of the documents that I said I was going to take pictures of and we're now concluding the interview.
Is there anything left that you would like to say?
Nothing more than that I have formulated my opinion from the evidence that I had at hand and through application thereof to the

The rules of criminal investigation have arrived at the conclusion that the party's name herein is members of a conspiracy in the assassination of John Fitzgerald Kennedy, deceased former president of the United States of America.

would be the uh most logical of any people and for the reasons herein stipulated to have entered into a conspiracy to have uh committed this offense okay it's 5 40 5 40 p.m on march the 12th 1980 and the interview has been the interview is completed
Today is March 13, 1980, and I'm just making this a follow-up note so that I don't forget on myself.

When I spoke with a man earlier, when I had spoken with the man the day before and I had talked to him earlier, he had said that Ruby had not enough control to outvote or at least cause the redirect in certain policies or principles in the Dallas police station.
Special notes to check.
Why?
had Jack Ruby, whom was a strip joint operator, been so close to the Dallas Police Department.
Also, on my initial interview, which was not recorded, which was the day before this original recording, I had been told that Johnson had instructed the motorcade route to be changed, and that
that Mr. Evans had been defaulted this information by and that Kennedy was only notified at the very last moment and was
The only reason that he went along with this is because Johnson said that Johnson had said or is reported to have conveniently talked him into that this change would be more politically profitable.

Special notes, which I'd like to make, just special notes, is Connolly's refusal to pardon Oswell, that Sanchez, who was the sheriff of Starr County, Coke Stevenson, Truman's pardon of par, Al Smith in 28, and it has not been mentioned, but it had been mentioned
by Conley that Kennedy's trip to Texas was dangerous.
Also, other points to note is why would Johnson accept the vice presidential nomination at the time he was Speaker at the House when the Speaker of the House is undisputedly considered
to have more authority or at least more of being in a position of persuasion if not his motives have been for more power.
Another point that I'd like to remember to investigate is did Ruby Clifton stop in between Mexico and why have none of the reports dealt with if he has or if he hasn't.
I'll say a note.
General Walker.
I want to find out more about him.
I was told, and I don't remember if this was on tape, that there was an attempt on his life.
A bullet hole went through his window and nearly missed him.
This is publicly acknowledged.
It can be found in most periodicals.
One other part that wasn't recorded that I've seen in my notes

that parr is indebted to lbj for 10 years of his life or there was in in reference to that i suppose that the alleged assassination conspiracy would have wiped out the debt uh also i cannot recollect correctly but there was some mention about the gun about
Oswald's gun having not been in normal custody after his apprehension for a couple of hours.
These couple of hours are lagging time, which are a point that needs to be investigated.
Nearly all the information on this tape is of course public knowledge and is the experience of one man who I consider to be of extremely high intelligence.
The fact that he has presented, he has presented well and he has at all times

adhered to his police mentality and police and prejudice and of using alleged and possible and probable and certain things are not common procedure conclusion mr. John B Evans has granted me the right to use any and every part of this interview for my research
I realize this interview does not bring to light any new evidence, but it does express some motives and circumstances that, in my opinion, deserve to be researched.
